                "HPGE"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " A shielded high purity germanium gamma-ray",
                "spectrometer"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ANALYSIS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The time-resolved gamma-ray information was used to",
                "identify decay products from the photoinduced fission",
                "of 238U. The nuclides were identified by their",
                "gamma-ray line energies and half-lives include 87,88Kr,",
                "92,93Sr, 93,94,95Y, 101,104Tc, 105Ru, 107Rh, 128Sb,",
                "128Sn,134Te, 135I, 138Xe, 138Cs, 141Ba, and 146Ce."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "CORRECTION": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The direct contribution to the yield of a given nuclide",
                "by the fission process was obtained from the total",
                "yield, after making corrections for contributions from",
                "other decay chains."
              ]
            }
          ],
